  "prompt": "How come people on Quora ask questions here, when they can get them on Google and why is Quora just a question/answer site, will it expand?",
  "response": "People often turn to Quora for answers instead of using Google for a few key reasons:\n\n1. **Specificity and Personalization**: Quora allows users to ask very specific questions and receive answers from individuals who may have personal experience or expertise on the subject. While Google can provide a wealth of information, it often requires sifting through various sources to find an answer that directly addresses the user's query. Quora's format enables direct, focused answers that can be more satisfying and relevant.\n\n2. **Human Interaction**: Quora provides a platform for human interaction, which can be more engaging than searching through web pages. Users can ask follow-up questions, clarify points, and engage in discussions, which can lead to a deeper understanding of the topic.\n\n3. **Diverse Perspectives**: On Quora, users can get answers from people with different backgrounds and perspectives. This diversity can be particularly valuable for complex or subjective questions where multiple viewpoints might be beneficial.\n\nRegarding Quora's format and potential expansion, here are a few points:\n\n1. **Core Functionality**: Quora's primary focus is on being a question-and-answer platform, and this focus has helped it build a dedicated user base. Its straightforward format makes it easy for users to find and share information.\n\n2. **Expansion and Diversification**: Quora has experimented with various features over the years to expand its functionality. For example, it introduced Quora Spaces, which allow users to create communities around specific topics, similar to social media groups. It also launched a blogging platform called Quora+, allowing users to write longer, in-depth posts.\n\n3. **Monetization Efforts**: Quora has introduced several monetization strategies, including a subscription model called Quora+ and an advertising platform. These efforts suggest that Quora is looking to expand its business model beyond just being a Q&A site.\n\n4. **Future Possibilities**: As for future expansions, Quora could potentially integrate more multimedia content, enhance its community features, or develop new tools for collaboration and knowledge sharing. However, any such expansions would need to align with Quora's mission of sharing and growing the world's knowledge.\n\nIn summary, while Quora currently operates as a question-and-answer site, it has already begun to diversify its offerings and may continue to do so in the future. The platform's success will depend on how well it balances its core functionality with new features that enhance the user experience.",
